WEBVTT

00:01.802 --> 00:03.604
- A Pop original series.

00:04.805 --> 00:07.775
[lively trumpet music]

00:07.808 --> 00:10.711
*

00:10.744 --> 00:11.679
- [gasps]

00:14.315 --> 00:15.716
I timed it perfectly.

00:15.749 --> 00:17.551
We arrived
at the exact same time.

00:17.585 --> 00:19.320
- Good morning, Penny.
- Good morning.

00:19.353 --> 00:20.554
- I think it's gonna be
a good day.

00:20.588 --> 00:22.356
- You look radiant.
- Oh.

00:22.390 --> 00:25.359
- Oh, my God, Wendy Williams
is gonna love your shoes.

00:25.393 --> 00:27.228
What time is the interview?
- I don't know.

00:27.261 --> 00:28.696
I have to look it up
when we get upstairs.

00:28.729 --> 00:30.264
- Okay.

00:30.298 --> 00:31.532
- I'm just kidding.
It's at 2:00.

00:31.565 --> 00:32.733
Ah, my stomach's
been in knots.

00:32.766 --> 00:34.568
I have been pooping
all night.

00:34.602 --> 00:35.736
- [chuckles]

00:35.769 --> 00:37.238
So, um, I know
that you didn't want

00:37.271 --> 00:39.140
anyone to know
that it's your birthday.

00:39.173 --> 00:40.608
- Oh, Penny, please,
I don't want

00:40.641 --> 00:43.077
some big office party
with awkward cake cutting,

00:43.111 --> 00:45.213
and I can't stand
the faces of everybody

00:45.246 --> 00:47.715
who can't afford to buy me
an expensive gift.

00:47.748 --> 00:49.150
- Well...

00:49.183 --> 00:51.085
I made this for you.

00:51.119 --> 00:52.253
- Ohh.

00:52.286 --> 00:53.554
- Make a wish.

00:53.587 --> 00:54.855
- All right.

00:54.888 --> 00:56.290
Should I close my eyes?

00:56.324 --> 00:58.159
- Close your eyes.
- Okay.

00:58.192 --> 00:59.260
[inhales sharply]

00:59.293 --> 01:00.628
[both gasp]

01:00.661 --> 01:03.331
- [scarfing and snorting]

01:05.299 --> 01:07.801
- Was that your wish?

01:07.835 --> 01:11.505
male announcer: From Studio 9B
in the heart of New York City,

01:11.539 --> 01:14.442
it's "Nightcap with Jimmy."

01:14.475 --> 01:16.810
Tonight, fresh from arresting
a sexual predator,

01:16.844 --> 01:19.313
Mariska Hargitay.

01:19.347 --> 01:23.151
Legendary director
Joel Schumacher.

01:23.184 --> 01:27.421
Todd the Tool
takes on Rosie Perez.

01:27.455 --> 01:29.790
And now, the man who's
number five in the ratings

01:29.823 --> 01:31.859
but number one in our hearts,

01:31.892 --> 01:33.861
here's Jimmy.

01:33.894 --> 01:37.831
[energetic brass music]

01:37.865 --> 01:41.469
- Who's everybody voting for
in the school board election?

01:41.502 --> 01:43.804
I like to be active
in my borough.

01:43.837 --> 01:44.905
- "Bore-ow"?
- "Burrow."

01:44.938 --> 01:46.307
- "Barrow."
- "Burrough."

01:46.340 --> 01:47.541
- "Bur-rog."
- Oh, hi, everyone.

01:47.575 --> 01:49.243
- Got to stop you
right there.

01:49.277 --> 01:51.345
Those shoes, not even close
to pulling them off.

01:51.379 --> 01:52.646
- Okay, Marcus,
you're not the only person

01:52.680 --> 01:54.282
that gets to dabble in fashion.

01:54.315 --> 01:55.883
- And genders.
- Watch it, ginger.

01:55.916 --> 01:57.485
- Okay, anyway, uh,

01:57.518 --> 01:59.187
big show, big show:

01:59.220 --> 02:01.322
Mariska Hargitay from "SVU,"

02:01.355 --> 02:02.823
we have the director
Joel Schumacher,

02:02.856 --> 02:04.325
"St. Elmo's Fire,"

02:04.358 --> 02:06.460
Guy the Snake Guy
with a 40-foot anaconda,

02:06.494 --> 02:07.895
and last, somehow Todd

02:07.928 --> 02:10.164
got Rosie Perez
to do a "Todd the Tool" sketch.

02:10.198 --> 02:11.699
So whoo!

02:11.732 --> 02:13.334
- I can't wait to see
what tool I get to play.

02:13.367 --> 02:14.702
I'm really hoping for a hammer.

02:14.735 --> 02:17.338
- Pretty great that we
landed Mariska, huh?

02:17.371 --> 02:19.340
- Big "SVU" fan, are we?

02:19.373 --> 02:20.574
- Yeah.
I mean, who isn't?

02:20.608 --> 02:21.942
It's on all day.
She's great.

02:21.975 --> 02:23.911
And the show's great.
It's a win-win.

02:23.944 --> 02:25.213
- Do you think she's pretty?

02:25.246 --> 02:26.380
- Yeah, she's pretty.

02:26.414 --> 02:27.481
- Really pretty?

02:27.515 --> 02:28.849
- Yes, she's really pretty.

02:28.882 --> 02:31.585
- Would you consider yourself
a stalker?

02:31.619 --> 02:32.920
- What?

02:32.953 --> 02:34.755
- Well, it has recently
come to my attention

02:34.788 --> 02:36.724
that I am supposed to be
protecting

02:36.757 --> 02:38.659
the guests of this show

02:38.692 --> 02:39.960
from stalkers.

02:39.993 --> 02:42.463
Now, I want you
to be honest with me.

02:42.496 --> 02:45.333
Do you plan on physically
attacking her?

02:45.366 --> 02:48.502
- No, Phil, I'm not planning
on attacking Mariska.

02:48.536 --> 02:50.571
- I've got my eye on you.

02:50.604 --> 02:52.540
- FYI, uh, Jimmy
talked to Mariska,

02:52.573 --> 02:54.342
and they worked out
a special surprise

02:54.375 --> 02:55.776
for tonight's show.

02:55.809 --> 02:57.678
- Well, what is it?
- Well, I don't know.

02:57.711 --> 02:58.746
Jimmy didn't tell me.

02:58.779 --> 02:59.880
- Great.
You know what?

02:59.913 --> 03:00.914
Fantastic.

03:00.948 --> 03:03.451
I have so much to do today,

03:03.484 --> 03:05.586
I'm happy to have Jimmy
take this off my plate.

03:05.619 --> 03:07.688
- You guys,
it's a really special day today.

03:07.721 --> 03:09.390
- Penny!
- Sorry.

03:09.423 --> 03:11.259
It's just normal special,
nothing big special.

03:11.292 --> 03:14.595
It's just so great to get
to work with you every day,

03:14.628 --> 03:16.564
to share an office
with you every day,

03:16.597 --> 03:19.233
to hang out with you all day,
and learn every day.

03:19.267 --> 03:21.635
- Do you think
she's pretty?

03:21.669 --> 03:23.304
Really pretty?

03:23.337 --> 03:24.838
- Obviously.

03:24.872 --> 03:26.707
- It's recently come
to my attention

03:26.740 --> 03:28.776
that I am supposed
to handle stalkers.

03:28.809 --> 03:30.478
Now I'm gonna ask you,
honestly,

03:30.511 --> 03:33.414
are you planning on
physically attacking her?

03:33.447 --> 03:35.449
*

03:35.483 --> 03:36.750
- Hey, gang.

03:36.784 --> 03:38.886
What are we talking about?

03:38.919 --> 03:40.388
- What's up, Todd?

03:40.421 --> 03:42.823
- You're looking
at a director.

03:42.856 --> 03:44.325
- We're looking at a tool.

03:44.358 --> 03:45.859
- No, no, director.

03:45.893 --> 03:47.528
Jimmy's allowing me to direct

03:47.561 --> 03:48.862
the "Todd the Tool" sketch
today.

03:48.896 --> 03:50.431
- Oh, my God, Todd,
that's huge.

03:50.464 --> 03:51.732
Congrats.
- Thank you.

03:51.765 --> 03:53.033
- Why are you telling us?

03:53.066 --> 03:54.902
- 'Cause we're friends.

03:54.935 --> 03:56.604
- Are we?
- Yeah.

03:56.637 --> 03:58.406
Besides Jimmy, you guys
are like my best friends.

03:58.439 --> 03:59.873
- Aw.

03:59.907 --> 04:01.375
We like you too, Todd.

04:01.409 --> 04:02.776
- Thank you.

04:02.810 --> 04:04.912
- I love the wood detailing
on your costume.

04:04.945 --> 04:06.447
- It's not real wood.

04:06.480 --> 04:07.848
It's too soft.

04:07.881 --> 04:11.885
*

04:11.919 --> 04:13.687
- Oh, Mariska.

04:13.721 --> 04:15.022
Staci. Hi.
- Hi, Staci.

04:15.055 --> 04:18.292
- It's so great
to have you on the show.

04:18.326 --> 04:20.428
I just got a call from Jimmy.
- Yeah.

04:20.461 --> 04:22.396
- Can I actually confirm
that you're okay

04:22.430 --> 04:24.298
being eaten by a snake
on the show?

04:24.332 --> 04:25.799
- Oh.
- Can I confirm this?

04:25.833 --> 04:27.635
- Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.
He called me last night.

04:27.668 --> 04:29.437
He told me all about it.
I'm totally game.

04:29.470 --> 04:31.004
- You weren't, uh, drinking?
- No, don't drink.

04:31.038 --> 04:32.906
- Okay, great.
- But, um, I'm--I'm game.

04:32.940 --> 04:34.342
I'm fun.
I'm fearless.

04:34.375 --> 04:36.410
- This day, of all days,
I can't have

04:36.444 --> 04:37.611
a celebrity die.

04:37.645 --> 04:38.912
- Look, I'm sure
that you have

04:38.946 --> 04:40.514
a million safety protocols
in place.

04:40.548 --> 04:42.015
- We actually don't.

04:42.049 --> 04:43.884
This is the first time
we've done this kind of shtick.

04:43.917 --> 04:45.353
But if you're game...
- Oh. [laughing]

04:45.386 --> 04:46.620
You're funny.

04:46.654 --> 04:47.921
I'm sure
it's gonna be fine.

04:47.955 --> 04:49.990
I'm sure it's
gonna be fine.

04:50.023 --> 04:51.425
*

04:51.459 --> 04:53.361
[dance music playing]

04:53.394 --> 04:55.329
- Hey, Todd,
what's with the music?

04:55.363 --> 04:57.498
- Uh, Tarantino
directs with music on,

04:57.531 --> 04:59.500
so...pbbt, boom.

04:59.533 --> 05:01.034
- Oh, great.
Thank you.

05:01.068 --> 05:02.470
- Shit gonna get cray.

05:02.503 --> 05:03.937
Hey, Rosie,
how you doing?

05:03.971 --> 05:05.373
- Hi.
- I'm Todd.

05:05.406 --> 05:06.774
How you doing?
- Oh, nice to meet you.

05:06.807 --> 05:09.377
And what do you do?
- Oh, I'm the director.

05:09.410 --> 05:10.844
- Oh, I thought
you were the tool.

05:10.878 --> 05:12.380
- [laughing] Oh, yeah.
- [laughs]

05:12.413 --> 05:13.647
- Let's get this baby
started, huh?

05:13.681 --> 05:15.015
All right.
- Okay.

05:15.048 --> 05:17.985
Um, so what exactly
are we doing in this sketch?

05:18.018 --> 05:21.522
Because all it said
was for us to be...

05:21.555 --> 05:23.691
you know, hilarious
and improv, so...

05:23.724 --> 05:25.058
- Yeah, I wrote that
just for you.

05:25.092 --> 05:26.527
You're gonna be great,
yeah.

05:26.560 --> 05:28.962
Just follow what it said
in the script, okay?

05:28.996 --> 05:30.464
All right, and action.

05:30.498 --> 05:32.065
- Got to wait for camera.

05:32.099 --> 05:33.701
- Oh, sorry.
I knew that.

05:33.734 --> 05:35.035
- Camera's ready.

05:35.068 --> 05:36.437
- And action.
- Wait.

05:36.470 --> 05:37.805
You got wait
for sound too, Todd.

05:37.838 --> 05:39.373
- Yeah, I knew that too.

05:39.407 --> 05:40.774
- Sound speeding.

05:40.808 --> 05:42.510
- And action.
- Uh, last looks, last looks.

05:42.543 --> 05:43.844
- Oh. [laughs]

05:43.877 --> 05:46.680
- All right, good.
She's good.

05:46.714 --> 05:47.781
- And action.

05:47.815 --> 05:49.917
- Sorry.
I'm looking for Staci.

05:49.950 --> 05:51.819
- Uh, yeah,
she's somewhere else.

05:51.852 --> 05:54.087
- Oh, she's probably running
around frantically somewhere.

05:54.121 --> 05:55.923
- Okay, I'll find her.
- Uh, excuse me, Mr. Schumacher.

05:55.956 --> 05:57.891
- Yeah?
- They have no idea who you are.

05:57.925 --> 05:59.159
Mr. Schumacher--
- Joel, please.

05:59.192 --> 06:00.861
- Joel, hi.
I'm Marcus.

06:00.894 --> 06:02.496
I can help you find Staci.

06:02.530 --> 06:04.097
- Hey, Marcus.
I can find her.

06:04.131 --> 06:05.633
- Uh, Mr. Schumacher?

06:05.666 --> 06:07.835
- Rosie Perez.
- You know me?

06:07.868 --> 06:09.169
- Of course.
You're Rosie Perez.

06:09.202 --> 06:10.471
So good to see you.
- Oh.

06:10.504 --> 06:12.406
Oh, nice to see you too.

06:12.440 --> 06:14.442
- Oh, I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to interrupt.

06:14.475 --> 06:16.176
But I love all your movies.

06:16.209 --> 06:18.446
- Oh, thank you.
I love all your movies too.

06:18.479 --> 06:19.747
- [nervously]
"Batman & Robin"?

06:19.780 --> 06:20.914
- Yeah.

06:20.948 --> 06:22.650
No.
[both laughing]

06:22.683 --> 06:23.884
- You're not that good
an actress.

06:23.917 --> 06:25.419
[both laughing]

06:25.453 --> 06:27.087
Anyway, it's so great
to see you all.

06:27.120 --> 06:29.723
Uh, you're into a skit
or something and...

06:29.757 --> 06:31.091
- That's right, yeah.
This is "Todd the Tool."

06:31.124 --> 06:33.093
I'm Todd.
- You're Todd the Tool.

06:33.126 --> 06:34.662
Can I watch, or is that--

06:34.695 --> 06:36.764
- Yeah, man.
You're famous.

06:36.797 --> 06:38.499
Sit down.
All right.

06:38.532 --> 06:40.701
This is green screen
back here.

06:40.734 --> 06:43.437
I was thinking, like,
that could be your apartment

06:43.471 --> 06:45.706
or specifically
your bathroom, 'cause--

06:45.739 --> 06:48.008
- Could I just
ask a question?

06:48.041 --> 06:50.010
Is there a script?
- It's all in my, uh--

06:50.043 --> 06:51.579
- So you're just--
you're winging it.

06:51.612 --> 06:53.046
- Yeah.
- Well, could we just

06:53.080 --> 06:54.782
deconstruct this?
Would you mind?

06:54.815 --> 06:57.551
So, Todd the Tool,
where were you born?

06:57.585 --> 06:58.619
- Long Island.

06:58.652 --> 06:59.687
- No, I don't mean you.

06:59.720 --> 07:01.622
I mean your character.

07:01.655 --> 07:03.691
- Oh, uh...

07:03.724 --> 07:05.493
the--the toolbox?

07:05.526 --> 07:07.661
- All right, what is
your purpose, then?

07:07.695 --> 07:08.862
You are a hammer.
- Yeah.

07:08.896 --> 07:09.997
- You're a tool,

07:10.030 --> 07:12.600
so you want to be
of service.

07:12.633 --> 07:14.935
You want to serve
people, right?

07:14.968 --> 07:16.470
- Wait, I--sorry.

07:16.504 --> 07:18.005
This isn't that funny,
you know?

07:18.038 --> 07:19.773
Like, no offense.

07:19.807 --> 07:21.509
I don't think you're really
a comedy director.

07:21.542 --> 07:22.976
I know comedy, though, so...

07:23.010 --> 07:24.478
- Why do you know comedy?

07:24.512 --> 07:25.679
- 'Cause I grew up with Jimmy

07:25.713 --> 07:27.247
and he thinks I'm funny

07:27.280 --> 07:29.249
and I laugh at a lot of things.

07:29.282 --> 07:31.018
- Well, you know,
when we're with our friends,

07:31.051 --> 07:32.753
we all think we're funny,
but it's different

07:32.786 --> 07:34.822
than really doing comedy
for an audience.

07:34.855 --> 07:36.490
- Absolutely, yeah.

07:36.524 --> 07:37.891
- Yeah, I agree too.

07:37.925 --> 07:40.794
Hey, good directors' minds
think alike.

07:40.828 --> 07:44.732
*

07:44.765 --> 07:47.000
- I like your choker.
- Oh, thanks.

07:47.034 --> 07:48.602
I wear it
'cause people like it.

07:48.636 --> 07:50.871
- That's why I wear things.
- Hi. Penny.

07:50.904 --> 07:53.674
- Staci,
this is Guy the Snake Guy.

07:53.707 --> 07:55.008
- Hi, Guy.
- Hi. Guy the Snake Guy.

07:55.042 --> 07:56.810
Nice to see you.
- Please tell me

07:56.844 --> 07:58.612
Mariska Hargitay's not gonna die
on "Nightcap" tonight.

07:58.646 --> 08:00.581
- I can't promise
that she's not gonna be killed.

08:00.614 --> 08:02.115
I mean, it's a big snake,
but, I mean,

08:02.149 --> 08:04.585
that's part of the intrigue,
isn't it, though, yeah?

08:04.618 --> 08:05.953
- [grunts]
- Okay.

08:05.986 --> 08:08.121
I'm here.
What's up in the hood?

08:08.155 --> 08:09.957
- Phil, um,
we're just going over

08:09.990 --> 08:11.592
with Guy the Snake Guy guy

08:11.625 --> 08:13.293
the Mariska Hargitay stunt.

08:13.326 --> 08:15.729
- "Everybody knows
I hate snakes."

08:15.763 --> 08:18.932
That's "Indiana Jones."

08:18.966 --> 08:20.300
- Phil, you need
to pay attention

08:20.333 --> 08:21.969
in case something
goes wrong.

08:22.002 --> 08:24.137
- Ah, I guess
I'll probably be ready.

08:24.171 --> 08:26.273
- Oh, Mariska, hi.
Oh, great.

08:26.306 --> 08:28.208
Um, this is Guy the Snake Guy.

08:28.241 --> 08:29.877
- So excited.
Happy to be here. Huge fan.

08:29.910 --> 08:31.144
- Yeah, you ready to be
a snake's dinner?

08:31.178 --> 08:32.946
- Yeah.
[both laughing]

08:32.980 --> 08:35.215
Funny.
- You sure you want to do this?

08:35.248 --> 08:36.784
- I'm absolutely sure.
It's gonna be fine.

08:36.817 --> 08:38.552
She's got to stop
talking me out of this.

08:38.586 --> 08:39.920
- It's just,
I don't want you to die.

08:39.953 --> 08:41.121
You've got, like,
15 kids.

08:41.154 --> 08:42.723
- I do.
It's gonna be fine.

08:42.756 --> 08:44.291
- Okay, well, Guy,
tell me if I'm wrong,

08:44.324 --> 08:47.027
but don't anacondas
eventually squeeze the life

08:47.060 --> 08:48.629
out of a human being?

08:48.662 --> 08:51.098
- Are you a snake expert
all of a sudden?

08:51.131 --> 08:52.299
- Ah.
- Seriously, Mariska,

08:52.332 --> 08:54.001
in the wild, these anacondas,

08:54.034 --> 08:57.204
they strangle their prey
lifeless and dead, yeah?

08:57.237 --> 08:58.906
And then they devour it.

08:58.939 --> 09:00.207
But not this snake.

09:00.240 --> 09:02.175
I've trained it
to skip the first step.

09:02.209 --> 09:04.311
Perfect. Just don't move.
- Okay, I won't move.

09:04.344 --> 09:06.313
But what--what if--
what if I move?

09:06.346 --> 09:08.248
- Crush your whole body.
It'd be a bloody mess.

09:08.281 --> 09:09.750
I mean horrible.

09:09.783 --> 09:11.184
- Oh, oh, okay.
Well, then I won't.

09:11.218 --> 09:13.286
I won't move.
- Yeah, don't move.

09:13.320 --> 09:15.122
- Okay.
[laughs]

09:15.155 --> 09:16.724
- You can't move.

09:16.757 --> 09:18.859
- Yeah, like, don't move.
Yeah, yeah.

09:18.892 --> 09:20.160
*

09:21.929 --> 09:25.599
[lively trumpet music]

09:25.633 --> 09:27.367
- All right, now,
this is how it's gonna go.

09:27.400 --> 09:29.036
Mariska's laying
down here, yeah?

09:29.069 --> 09:30.804
And I've trained the snake

09:30.838 --> 09:32.706
to start on
the special material

09:32.740 --> 09:35.308
and swallow all the way
up to the top right around here.

09:35.342 --> 09:37.010
You comfortable with that?
- Yep, got it.

09:37.044 --> 09:38.846
- Now, to make sure that you're
good under pressure...

09:38.879 --> 09:40.080
- Mm-hmm.

09:40.113 --> 09:41.381
- I'm gonna pretend
I'm the snake.

09:41.414 --> 09:43.651
Just as a little test, yeah?
- Got it.

09:43.684 --> 09:44.918
- The snake starts out
right here.

09:44.952 --> 09:46.353
- Mm-hmm.
- Yeah, it's not moving.

09:46.386 --> 09:47.921
What's going on?
How's this gonna work?

09:47.955 --> 09:48.989
I don't know.
Is it asleep?

09:49.022 --> 09:50.223
Bam!
- Oh, God!

09:50.257 --> 09:52.359
- See?
And that's how fast it is.

09:52.392 --> 09:54.361
Right up on your ankles
there, Mariska.

09:54.394 --> 09:55.696
- Mm-hmm.
- Yeah, a little tight.

09:55.729 --> 09:56.897
A little sticky, a little slimy.

09:56.930 --> 09:58.932
Right up again.
